# Keep GitHub's downloadable archives limited to the plugin itself.
#
# `git archive` powers both the "Code -> Download ZIP" button and each release's
# auto-generated "Source code" assets. Anything marked `export-ignore` is dropped
# from that output, so a downloaded source archive contains only the plugin
# subdirectory — not the CI config, dev docs, or git metadata that would ride
# along otherwise. The recommended install is the named `<slug>-X.Y.Z.zip` release
# asset, which the workflow builds from the plugin subtree.
/.github        export-ignore
/.gitignore     export-ignore
/.gitattributes export-ignore
/CLAUDE.md      export-ignore
/README.md      export-ignore
